sql:
SELECT COUNT(sequence_id) AS total_active_sequences
FROM sequences
WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT COUNT(sequence_id) AS total_shared_sequences
FROM shared_sequences
WHERE shared_by = 'alice.smith@example.com';

SELECT sequence
FROM sequences
WHERE sequence_id = '1';

external_knowledge:
; Research groups refer to collaborative teams working on genetic sequence projects; 
; A shared genetic sequence is one that has been made accessible to multiple research groups; 
; A viewed genetic sequence refers to one that has been accessed by a user with 'view' or 'download' access type.

sql:
SELECT sequence_id, structure_prediction, binding_affinity, motif_score
FROM sequences
WHERE species_id = 'some_species_id';

SELECT sequence_id, structure_prediction, binding_affinity, motif_score, gene_prediction
FROM sequences
WHERE status = 'active' AND binding_affinity > 0.5;

SELECT annotation_value
FROM sequence_annotations
WHERE annotation_type = 'function';

external_knowledge:
- 'Crown jewels of genetic sequences' refers to the top 3 most accessed sequences; 
- 'unearthed' refers to the user who shared the sequence; 
- 'research fellowship' refers to the research group the sequences were shared with; 
- 'sequence blueprints' are the actual genetic sequences; 
- 'how many times they've been unearthed' refers to the access count.
